Chicken Piccata
  --Cook's Illustrated

4 6-8oz boneless, skinless chicken breasts, trimmed
kosher salt and pepper
2 large lemons
3/4 c ap flour
1/4 c + 1 tsp vegetable oil
1 shallot, minced
1 garlic clove, minced
1 c chicken broth
3 tbsp unsalted butter, cut into 6 pieces
2 tbsp capers, drained
1 tbsp minced fresh parsley

Cut each chicken breast in half crosswise, then cut thick half in half again horizontally, creating 3 cutlets of similar thickness. Place cutlets between sheets of plastic wrap and gently pount to even 1/2" thickness. Place cutlets in bowl and toss with 2 tsp salt and 1/2 tsp pepper. Set aside for 15 min. Halve 1 lemon lengthwise, trim ends from 1 half, halve lengthwise again, then cut crosswise 1/4" thick slices; set aside. Juice remaining half and whole lemon and set aside 3 tbsp juice. Spread flour in shallow dish. Working with 1 cutlet at a time, dredge cutlets in flour, shaking gently to remove excess. Place on wire rack set in rimmed baking sheet. Heat 2 tbsp oil in 12" skillet over medium high heat until smoking. Place 6 cutlets in skillet, reduce heat to medium, and cook until golden brown on 1 side, 2-3 min. Flip and cook until golden brown on second side, 2-3 min. Return cutlets to wire rack. Repeat with 2 tbsp oil and remaining 6 cutlets. Add remaining 1 tsp oil and shallot to skillet and cook until softened, 1 min. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 30 s. Add broth, reserved lemon juice, and reserved lemon slices and bring to simmer, scraping up any fond. Add cutlets to sauce and simmer for 4 min, flipping halfway through simmering. Transfer cutlets to platter. Sauce should be thickedn to consistency of heavy cream; if not, simmer 1 min longer. Off heat, whisk in butter, stir in capers and parsley. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.


Notes: Serve with buttered pasta, rice, potatoes, or crusty bread and a simple steamed vegetable.
